---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Indigo Business Solutions"
  description="Our policies and procedures for collection, use, and disclosure of information when using Indigo Business Solutions services."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="crumb">Home Page / Privacy Policy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <a href="/contact-us/" class="cta">Free evaluation</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="policy shell">
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes our policies and procedures on the
      collection, use, and disclosure of your information when you use the
      Service and tells you about your privacy rights and how the law protects
      you.
    </p>
    <p>
      We use your personal data to provide and improve the Service. By using the
      Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance
      with this Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Interpretation and Definitions</h2>
    <h3>Interpretation</h3>
    <p>
      Words with initial capitalization have meanings defined under the
      following conditions. These definitions have the same meaning whether they
      appear in singular or plural form.
    </p>

    <h3>Definitions</h3>
    <p>For the purposes of this Privacy Policy:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Account</strong> means a unique account created for you to access
        our Service or parts of our Service.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Company</strong> refers to Indigo Business Solutions.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cookies</strong> are small files placed on your device containing
        details of browsing history and similar usage.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Country</strong> refers to the United States.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Device</strong> means any device that can access the Service (computer,
        mobile phone, tablet).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Personal Data</strong> means information that relates to an identified
        or identifiable individual.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Service</strong> refers to the Website.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Service Provider</strong> means any natural or legal person processing
        data on behalf of the Company to facilitate, provide, or analyze use of the
        Service.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Usage Data</strong> means data collected automatically from use of
        the Service.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Website</strong> refers to <a href="https://indigousa.com/"
          >https://indigousa.com/</a
        >.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>You</strong> means the individual or legal entity using the Service.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Collecting and Using Your Personal Data</h2>
    <h3>Types of Data Collected</h3>
    <h4>Personal Data</h4>
    <p>
      While using our Service, we may ask you to provide personally identifiable
      information, including but not limited to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>First name and last name</li>
      <li>Phone number</li>
      <li>Usage data</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Usage Data</h4>
    <p>
      Usage Data is collected automatically when using the Service. It may
      include IP address, browser type/version, pages visited, time and date of
      visit, time spent on pages, unique device identifiers, and diagnostic
      data.
    </p>
    <p>
      When the Service is accessed by mobile device, we may collect device type,
      unique mobile device ID, mobile OS, mobile browser type, and other
      diagnostic data.
    </p>

    <h3>Tracking Technologies and Cookies</h3>
    <p>
      We use cookies and similar tracking technologies (such as beacons, tags,
      and scripts) to track activity and store certain information to improve
      and analyze our Service.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cookies or Browser Cookies:</strong> You can instruct your browser
        to refuse cookies, but some parts of the Service may not function without
        them.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Web Beacons:</strong> Small electronic files that help count users,
        measure activity, and verify system integrity.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>We use both Session and Persistent Cookies, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Necessary / Essential Cookies (Session):</strong> Required to provide
        core Website services and prevent fraudulent use.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Notice Acceptance Cookies (Persistent):</strong> Identify whether
        users accepted cookie use.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Functionality Cookies (Persistent):</strong> Remember your choices
        and improve user experience.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Use of Your Personal Data</h3>
    <p>The Company may use personal data to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and maintain the Service, including usage monitoring.</li>
      <li>Manage your account and registration.</li>
      <li>Perform contracts related to products and services.</li>
      <li>Contact you by email, phone, SMS, and similar communications.</li>
      <li>
        Send news, special offers, and service updates unless you opt out.
      </li>
      <li>Manage your requests and support inquiries.</li>
      <li>Evaluate or complete business transfers.</li>
      <li>Analyze trends and improve products, services, and marketing.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We may share personal information with service providers, affiliates,
      business partners, or with your consent, and as needed for business
      transfers.
    </p>

    <h3>Retention of Your Personal Data</h3>
    <p>
      We retain personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes
      described in this policy, including legal compliance, dispute resolution,
      and enforcement of agreements.
    </p>

    <h3>Transfer of Your Personal Data</h3>
    <p>
      Your information may be processed at Company operating offices or other
      locations where processing parties are located, and may be transferred
      across jurisdictions with different data protection laws.
    </p>
    <p>
      By submitting information, you consent to this transfer. We take
      reasonable steps to ensure secure treatment consistent with this Privacy
      Policy.
    </p>

    <h3>Disclosure of Your Personal Data</h3>
    <h4>Business Transactions</h4>
    <p>
      If the Company is involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale,
      personal data may be transferred with notice before transfer.
    </p>
    <h4>Law Enforcement</h4>
    <p>
      We may disclose personal data if required by law or valid requests from
      public authorities.
    </p>
    <h4>Other legal requirements</h4>
    <p>We may disclose personal data in good faith to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      <li>Protect rights or property of the Company</li>
      <li>Prevent or investigate wrongdoing related to the Service</li>
      <li>Protect user or public safety</li>
      <li>Protect against legal liability</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Security of Your Personal Data</h3>
    <p>
      We use commercially acceptable means to protect personal data, but no
      method of transmission or storage is 100% secure and absolute security
      cannot be guaranteed.
    </p>

    <h3>Children&apos;s Privacy</h3>
    <p>
      Our Service does not address anyone under age 13. We do not knowingly
      collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe a child
      provided data, contact us so we can remove it.
    </p>

    <h3>Links to Other Websites</h3>
    <p>
      Our Service may contain links to third-party websites not operated by us.
      We are not responsible for third-party content, privacy policies, or
      practices and recommend reviewing those policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes are effective
      when posted on this page. You are advised to review this policy
      periodically.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us by phone at <a
        href="tel:+16316309845">(631) 630-9845</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style lang="less">
  .shell {
    width: min(1120px, 94%);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: clamp(5.6rem, 8vw, 8rem) 0 2.4rem;
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, #12183f 0%, #1e2868 56%, #344494 100%);
    border-bottom-left-radius: 3rem;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3rem;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .crumb {
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: #c8cfee;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: #fff;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.8vw, 3.2rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }

  .cta {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.58rem 1.04rem;
    background: #fff;
    color: #1b245d;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }

  .policy {
    padding: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.5rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    max-width: 88ch;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.1rem);
    margin: 1.6rem 0 0.55rem;
    color: #223164;
  }

  .policy h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 0.4rem;
    color: #2d3f77;
  }

  .policy h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0.3rem;
    color: #334886;
  }

  .policy p,
  .policy li {
    color: #3e4a7f;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .policy ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.6rem;
  }

  .policy a {
    color: #2445a0;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .policy a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
